# Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) in Python

Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) in Python allows developers to create modular, reusable, and scalable code structures by defining classes and objects. 
OOP concepts such as inheritance, encapsulation, polymorphism, and abstraction help in designing efficient solutions to complex problems. 
By mastering these principles, developers can build applications that are easier to maintain and extend over time.

This repository provides an defination of key OOP concepts in Python, including classes, objects, inheritance, polymorphism, encapsulation, and abstraction. 

